# A [[metric]] for objects on the scale of [[quadrillion]]s (10<sup>15</sup> or 1,000,000,000,000,000) of elements. Most often used for computer systems; a [[petascale]] computer system operates at speeds measured in [[petaflop]]s and has memory measured in [[petabyte]]s.

